reviewText:
Random PewDiePie picture in a locker that you can fap to, so that's just dandy.

This isn't the worst game I've ever played or anything. The first 2 levels start out really slow. One of your weapons is a piece of paper... that's right, paper cut your enemies into submission. The 3rd level actually picks up and you kill some monsters, but the game lacks direction on the levels. I ran around for a half hour trying to find the next door I needed to go through and then just gave up. I'm VERY easily scared, but even this game got boring very quickly. Also, if you don't figure out that you manually need to save, you'll die and go back to the very beginning of the game... So that was cool.

Here is my playthrough of Lvl 1-3:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jmtlrxKTIFw

reviewText:
I haven't finished the game yet - I don't know how long it is, so far it's been around 40 minutes of me playing it.  If you wanna see what playing the game looks like before buying it, here's some gameplay: https://youtu.be/GS-jja2VVVw part 2 is currently rendering right now.

It's a fun game so far, pretty scary.  Here are some pros and cons

Pros:
Very easy game to run.  Not laggy at all.
Graphics are nice.
Exciting to play.
Shooting mechanics are good, except the enemies can endure a lot of bullets, which is a bit annoying.
Overall, good game

Cons:
When I try to ALT TAB out of the game it won't let me, which is annoying.
Like I said, the enemies can endure a lot of damage.

AND that's pretty much it! Like I said, good game so far.  I don't know how long it is, but I'm excited to finish it.
